<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-03-27T20:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-03-27T20:00:00-05:00" n="594" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d594">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 337.11/350</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-03-27T20:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 27, 1917, 8 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Cuba Company reports to Department 1,500 rebels visited Jobabo, Oriente
                            Province March 18, looting and destroying property, threatening
                            destruction to mill. American and British employees in danger. Have no
                            reports since eighteenth.</p>
                        <p>Investigate as to conditions at Jobabo, and advise Department what
                            efforts Cuban Government is making for protection there.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>